linux command
create directory:

    mkdir <dirname>   (this command is use to create the directory)
    mkdir <dir1><dir2><dir3>  (use to create multiple directory)
    mkdir -p <dir1><dir2><dir3>  (use to create hirerchical directory)
    cd <dir> (Used to change the current working directory to the specified directory)

list 
    ls  (This command is used to list files and directories in the current directory)
    ls -l  (Used to display files and directories in long format with permissions, owner, size, and date)
    ls -a  (Used to display all files including hidden files)
    ls -la  (Used to display all files including hidden files in long format)  
    ls -h  (Used to display file sizes in human-readable format)
    ls -R  (Used to list files and directories recursively)
    ls -t  (Used to sort files and directories by modification time)
    ls <directory_name> (Used to list files and directories inside the specified directory)

Create file 
    touch <filename>            # Used to create an empty file
    touch <file1> <file2> <file3>  # Used to create multiple files at the same time
    nano <filename>    # Used to create or edit a file using nano editor
        we use ctrl+s (to save the file) and ctrl+x (to exit the editor)
    vi <filename>      # Used to create or edit a file using vi editor
        we use esc and :wq to (save and exit the editor) w=save and q=quit

view file
    cat <filename>            # Used to display the content of a file
    cat <file1> <file2>       # Used to display contents of multiple files
    cat > <filename>          # Used to create a file and write content
    cat >> <filename>         # Used to append content to an existing file
    cat -n <filename>         # Used to display file content with line numbers
    ctrl+d (is used to exit the editor)













    
